       There Is No Planet B
       Step up to protect the nature we need to thrive
       Donate Now
       © Flavio Forner / Conservation International


   People need nature — and for over 30 years, Conservation International
   has worked to protect it. Through cutting-edge science, innovative
   pol​​icy and global reach, we empower people to protect the nature that
   we rely on for food, fresh water and livelihoods.

   Learn More About Conservation International


Latest Conservation News

   Science

Climate breakdown is here. It’s time to adapt. But how?

   Fundamental shifts may be necessary to adapt to climate breakdown.

   View all posts about: Science
   Climate Change

Climate Week: Youth, morality and the fate of the Amazon

   Monday's Climate Week roundup: France commits US$ 100 million to a fund
   to protect the Amazon, religious leaders discuss the ethics of
   conservation and scientists declare a "planetary emergency."

   View all posts about: Climate Change
   Forests

Four questions about the Amazon fires, answered

   Conservation International experts explain more about the fires raging
   through the Amazon.

   View all posts about: Forests
   Biodiversity

‘Ecological SWAT team’ documents treasures from a lost city

   A team of scientists completed a biological survey of the “White City”
   of Honduras, a recently discovered set of ancient ruins deep within the
   Mosquitia rainforest.

   View all posts about: Biodiversity
   Oceans

Climate crisis pushing oceans to the brink, report warns

   The new UN report warns that climate change could have a drastic impact
   on the world's oceans and, in turn, humanity.

   View all posts about: Oceans
   Indigenous Peoples

Meet 3 indigenous women fighting to save the planet

   On the International Day of the World’s Indigenous People, we share the
   stories of three indigenous women fighting to protect the environment.

   View all posts about: Indigenous Peoples

Protecting the Planet that Provides

   Through cutting-edge science, policy and partnerships, we inform smart
   decisions for protecting nature — while providing the funding, training
   and expertise to make it all possible. With offices in more than 30
   countries, we work directly with the people who live closest to the
   forests, oceans and grasslands that benefit us all.
   1,200
   protected areas across 77 countries
   2,000+
   partners in more than 30 countries
   601
   million hectares of land, marine and coastal areas protected
   Together we can protect nature for the benefit of everyone.
   Donate Now

   IFRAME: https://www.youtube.com/embed/h6bTR0Y45Rw


Take a stand for nature

   Conserving nature and its benefits is an imperative, not a luxury. Join
   the many people who support our conservation efforts around the globe.

Make a Monthly Donation

   Make a tax-deductible donation and help protect the nature we rely on.
   Donate Now

Join the Emerald Circle

   Emerald Circle members provide us with the core financial support we
   need to fulfill our mission.
   Learn More

